<subSubSection pageId="137" pageNumber="752" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="137.[2094,2682,1812,2230]" lastBlockId="137.[1479,2683,2238,3449]" pageId="137" pageNumber="708">
Maxwell's Duiker is sometimes included in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Thunberg" baseAuthorityYear="1789" box="[2139,2301,1921,1954]" class="Mammalia" family="Bovidae" genus="Philantomba" kingdom="Animalia" order="Artiodactyla" pageId="137" pageNumber="708" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="monticola">P. monticola</taxonomicName>
(particularly in historical reports), although it is now well recognized as a separate species. Reports prior to 2010 listed Maxwell’s Duiker as present from 
<collectingCountry box="[2175,2284,2079,2112]" name="Gambia" pageId="137" pageNumber="708">Gambia</collectingCountry>
to 
<collectingCountry box="[2333,2438,2079,2112]" name="Nigeria" pageId="137" pageNumber="708">Nigeria</collectingCountry>
, but populations from 
<collectingCountry box="[2183,2254,2118,2151]" name="Togo" pageId="137" pageNumber="708">Togo</collectingCountry>
eastwards have been determined to be specifically distinct and are listed under Verheyen’s Duiker (FP. wal teri). Two subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="137" pageNumber="752" type="multiple">
